    "Applying this method on a current radar scan, a robot can recognize the revisited LiDAR submaps.",
    "Traditional 3D-PCPR methods assume that reliable prior maps are available.",
    "Tang et al. (2021) proposed a different approach which assumes that an overhead view of the workspace is available instead.",
    "The overhead view is used as a map for radar and LiDAR based localization.",
    "Their method consists of three steps: rotation inference, image generation, and pose estimation."
